                            <h3>Algorithm: </h3>
                            <h5>Displayed Parts only have a processing capability greater than the # of bits per second of information you need to transmit and can handle more millions of instructions per second than your mission needs. Bits per Second can be calculated by our program in the 3 ways shown below:</h5>
                            <h5>Bits per Second = # Channels x Bits/Channel x Integrations per second</h4>
                            <h5>Bits per Second = (pixel array in x direction) * (pixel array in y direction) *  (Integrations per second)</h4>
                            <h5>Bits per Second = inputted Bits/Second</h4>
                            <h3>What to Do:</h3>
